external_knowledge:
- "Age group" refers to a categorized range of ages, such as '0-10', '11-20', etc.;
- "Medical condition" refers to a specific health issue or disease;
- "Petals (patients)" is a metaphorical term for the number of patients in each age group with a specific medical condition.

- "the garden of health" refers to the database of patient records;
- "drinking the elixir of life" refers to the patients being exposed to drugs;
- "herbs they are tending to" refers to the covariates being measured;
- "in the year of the tiger" refers to the year 2022.
